# Dockerized Python App Template

This project provides a template for a Dockerized Python application. You can either build the image locally or pull a pre-built image from the GitHub Container Registry.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Docker
- Docker Compose

### Clone the Repository

```sh
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/dockerized-python-app-template.git
cd dockerized-python-app-template
```

### Fill the .env File

Create a .env file in the root directory of the project and fill it with the necessary environment variables. Here is an example:

```# .env
ENV_VAR1=value1
ENV_VAR2=value2
```

### Running the App

#### Build and Run Locally

To build the image locally and run the app, use the following command:

```docker-compose up python-app-template```

#### Pull and Run Pre-built Image

To pull the pre-built image from the GitHub Container Registry and run the app, use the following command:

```docker-compose up python-app-template-prebuilt```

### Stopping the App

To stop the app, press Ctrl+C in the terminal where the app is running, or use the following command in another terminal:
```docker-compose down```

